This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically the use of RNNs for text normalization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of different RNN architectures and the potential for better solutions from the community, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a filter to mitigate errors, which could fall under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SD) or signal processing (cs.SI).
